The paper deals with the problem of distinct value estimation in databases, which is a core topic in the field of database systems (cs.DB). The study is empirical and involves large-scale data analysis, which suggests that the paper could also be classified under the sub-category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper uses statistical approaches to solve the problem, which could also place it under the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the commercial impact of the problem, which could make it relevant to the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper deals with the issue of error in sampling-based estimators, which could also make it relevant to the sub-category of information theory (cs.IT).
